Explain in your own words and examples, what is Shell Scripting for DevOps.

Shell Scripting for devops generally user for automation purpose.Scripting genrally contain set of command with condition/control flow .So if there are some task which needs to be done repetative without human intervention to reduce human effort/error we put those task in the script and then run acoordingly either maunlly or with the help crontab.

What is #!/bin/bash? can we write #!/bin/sh as well?

#!/bin/bash repesent the interpreter it basically which shell is going to run mention command.

#!/bin/sh - yes its also represent shell.

Write a Shell Script which prints I will complete #90DaysOofDevOps challenge

[dheeraj@localhost shell_script]$ ./devops_challenge.sh
I will complete #90DaysOofDevOps challenge
[dheeraj@localhost shell_script]$ date
Fri Jul 28 10:33:47 IST 2023
[dheeraj@localhost shell_script]$ cat devops_challenge.sh
#!/bin/bash

echo "I will complete #90DaysOofDevOps challenge"
[dheeraj@localhost shell_script]$


Write a Shell Script to take user input, input from arguments and print the variables

[dheeraj@localhost shell_script]$ ./input_output.sh
Enter your name : Dheeraj
Your Name is Dheeraj
Enter password : your password is 123
[dheeraj@localhost shell_script]$ cat input_output.sh
#!/bin/bash

read -p "Enter your name : " Name
echo "Your Name is $Name"

read -s -p "Enter password : " password
echo "your password is $password "
[dheeraj@localhost shell_script]$ date
Fri Jul 28 10:40:59 IST 2023
[dheeraj@localhost shell_script]$


Write an Example of If else in Shell Scripting by comparing 2 numbers

[dheeraj@localhost shell_script]$ cat comparision.sh
#!/bin/bash

read -p "Enter the first Number :" x
read -p "Enter the second Numer :" y

if [ $x -lt $y ]
then
   echo "y is grater than x"
else
   echo "x is grater than y"
fi
[dheeraj@localhost shell_script]$ date
Fri Jul 28 11:06:02 IST 2023
[dheeraj@localhost shell_script]$
